# PR Notes – Chat Assistant + Local AI

What I changed
- Added chat assistant flow with predefined support replies then fallback to local AI (OllamaClient).
- Implemented database-backed queries: “reports/detections” with date parsing.
- Built a small Flask wrapper so Android can call the host via 10.0.2.2.
- Increased OkHttp timeouts and added logging + error handling messages.
- Created /app/docs/screenshots and added emulator screenshots for evidence.
- Wrote a developer README with run instructions for reviewers.

Why this matters
- Proves end-to-end chat works on device (UI → local DB → Flask → Ollama).
- Gives mentors a repeatable way to run the demo and verify evidence.

Follow-ups
- Make model name configurable.
- Add health-check ping before sending a prompt.
- Swap to a smaller model if RAM is low, or stream long answers.
